<StringTableFile>
  <Name>conversations\01_defiance_bay_copperlane\01_cv_hamor</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>22</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You asked me for one and I said no, not until you're older and more responsible. Do you remember this conversation?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>Gordy's eyes are fixed on the ground in front of him. "Yes, sir."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And yet I find you out here, playing with a blade that CLEARLY belongs to the Knights. Do you see the problem?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I didn't steal it, honest! I traded a secret for it." He points at you. "Ask him!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>"I didn't steal it, honest! I traded a secret for it." He points at you. "Ask her!"</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>Hamor turns to you. "Is what my son says true?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"He wants to be a Crucible Knight. I thought it was a good way to get him started in an honorable profession."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Lie] "I've never met this boy before."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It sure is. What are you going to do about it?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"He's lying! He was the one who-"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>"She's lying! She was the one who-"</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You just don't know when to stop, do you, boy? Well, guess what? You're cleaning the chamberpots in the Goose and Fox for three weeks."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"But that's not fair!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Now it's four weeks. Want to make it five? Go ahead, open your mouth again."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>He stares at you for a moment, then shakes his head. "Well, I still don't approve of my boy having a weapon, but I'm glad he's no thief."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You can keep the blade, but I'll be holding onto it until you're a squire with the Knights."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Come along, Gordy. I won't have you loitering out here all day."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>He starts to say something, then thinks better of it.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes, it is."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"He's just a boy, do you understand me? What were you thinking, getting him a blade like that? You stay away from him from now on."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>Gordy swallows but remains silent.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Good. Now march on over to the inn. Your punishment starts now."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm sorry my boy tried to get you in trouble."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Gordy's always been a little willful and headstrong."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>